          <lastSummaryUpdateDate>2019-03-12T20:53:37Z</lastSummaryUpdateDate>
          <text><![CDATA[<p><b>Stop the Tax Hike on Charities and Places of Worship Act </b></p> <p>This bill modifies the requirements for determining the unrelated business taxable income of tax-exempt organizations. The bill repeals a provision that requires unrelated business taxable income to be increased by the amount of expenses paid or incurred by a tax-exempt organization for certain fringe benefits for which a tax deduction is not allowed, including benefits relating to transportation, parking, or an on-premises athletic facility. </p> <p>The bill also increases the corporate income tax rate from 21% to 22%. </p>]]></text>
          <updateDate>2019-02-14T05:00:00Z</updateDate>
          <name>Introduced in Senate</name>
        </item>
      </billSummaries>
